<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="B" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Bridge" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Bridge,</orth> 1) a building raised over water for the convenience of passage: <bibl n="shak. ado 1.1.318" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado I, 1, 318</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 1h4 4.3.70" default="NO" valid="yes">H4A IV, 3, 70</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 6, 2</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 6, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 6, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 6, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. h5 3.6.2" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 III, 6, 2</bibl> <bibl n="shak. 1h6 1.4.67" default="NO" valid="yes">H6A I, 4, 67</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.4.49" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B IV, 4, 49</bibl> <cit><quote>(London b.).</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.5.3" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 5, 3</bibl></cit>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.2.72" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 2, 72</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. lr 3.4.58" default="NO" valid="yes">Lr. III, 4, 58</bibl>.<lb />2) the bony part of the nose: <cit><quote>down with the nose, down with it flat; take the b. quite away of him that . . . .,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tim 4.3.157" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. IV, 3, 157</bibl></cit>.
